attributeList.attribute: INTerAction database (IntAct) provides an open source database and toolkit for the storage, presentation and analysis of molecular interactions.
European Bioinformatics Institute; Wellcome Trust Genome Campus; Hinxton, Cambridge; CB10 1SD; United Kingdom
A collection of literature-mined stable and functionally defined human molecular complexes of known stoichiometry and biological role.

names.alias: Global genome repair CUL3-RAD7-RAD16-ELC1 ubiquitin ligase complex

attributeList.attribute: A ubiquitin ligase complex required for optimal nucleotide excision repair following UV-induced DNA damage. Ubiquinates the DNA repair protein RAD4 (P14736), targeting it for degradation by the 26S proteasome following UV radiation. de novo protein synthesis subsequently restores RAD4 to pre-irradiation levels.
